    "liam_scene_intro_silent": "There are days when the city feels open. And there are days when it reminds you that it is not for everyone. I could stay in this room, but today I need to go out into the city.",
    "liam_route_briefing": "Movement begins with planning. Take a photo of the path ahead of you - not as it should be, but as it really is.",
    "liam_route_title": "Route",
    "liam_route_prompt": "Take a photo of the path ahead of you - not idealized, but exactly as it is.",
    "liam_route_tag_prompt": "What did you notice? Choose a tag that will shape the story of this space.",
    "liam_route_education": "Accessibility is when you do not have to think through every step.",
    "liam_obstacle_briefing": "For some, it is just a small thing. For me, it is an obstacle. Find and photograph what blocks the way.",
    "liam_obstacle_title": "Obstacle",
    "liam_obstacle_prompt": "Find and photograph what blocks the way.",
    "liam_obstacle_tag_prompt": "Choose a tag that shows the impact of the barrier on a wheelchair user.",
    "liam_obstacle_education": "Barriers are often invisible to those who do not experience them.",
    "liam_boundary_npc": "Oh, let me help.",
    "liam_boundary_stop": "Stop.",
    "liam_boundary_choice_prompt": "Choose Liam's response.",
    "liam_boundary_choice_explain": "Explain",
    "liam_boundary_choice_joke": "Joke",
    "liam_boundary_choice_sharp": "Respond sharply",
    "liam_boundary_response_explain": "Thanks, but ask first. My wheelchair is my personal space.",
    "liam_boundary_response_joke": "Careful, this is manual control. Driving without permission comes with a fine.",
    "liam_boundary_response_sharp": "Hands off. I decide when and where I move.",
    "liam_boundary_title": "Control and Boundaries",
    "liam_boundary_prompt": "I'm not against help - I'm against people deciding for me. Photograph a space or situation where your choice is taken away.",
    "liam_boundary_tag_prompt": "Choose a tag for the shot.",
    "liam_boundary_education": "Help without consent is a boundary violation. Ask first, then help.",
    "liam_comments_intro": "Comments begin to scroll under Liam's post:\n\n\"How did you even get here?\"\n\"Wow, can you actually get there in a wheelchair?\"\n\"Did someone help you get there?\"\n\"You're so brave for going out at all.\"\n\"A real hero. I wouldn't be able to do that in your place.\"\n\"Honestly, I was looking at the wheelchair before the photo.\"\n\"Careful, the pavement there is uneven. Don't get stuck.\"\n\"I don't know what is more impressive - the place or the fact that you're there.\"\n\"It must be really hard for you to create this kind of content.\"\n\"It's great that you're not just staying at home.\"",
    "liam_self_briefing": "Personality is always greater than limitation. Take a selfie, 'I Am More.' Show your style and character without any stereotypes.",
    "liam_self_title": "Self-Expression",
    "liam_self_prompt": "Take a selfie, 'I Am More.' Show your style and character without any stereotypes.",
    "liam_self_tag_prompt": "Choose a tag for the shot.",
    "liam_self_education": "Limitations exist in spaces and in other people's stereotypes, but not in your personality.",
    "liam_almost_briefing": "Here is that familiar feeling: a place seems so close, yet you still cannot reach it - and it is not your fault. Take a photo called 'Almost There' and capture what remains out of reach.",
    "liam_almost_title": "Almost There",
    "liam_almost_prompt": "Capture what remains out of reach.",
    "liam_almost_tag_prompt": "Choose a tag for the shot.",
    "liam_almost_education": "Most barriers arise from design mistakes, not necessity.",
    "liam_space_briefing": "Sometimes, making a space more accessible takes just one simple action. Remove what blocks the way and take the final photo, 'Space at Eye Level.'",
    "liam_space_title": "Space at Eye Level",
    "liam_space_prompt": "Take the final photo, 'Space at Eye Level.'",
    "liam_space_tag_prompt": "Choose a tag for the shot.",
    "liam_space_education": "Inclusion is not an extraordinary effort, but a conscious step toward comfort for everyone.",
    "liam_final_dialog": "You can see it now - the things most people never notice. And that already changes more than it seems.",
    "liam_final_education": "Do not reduce a wheelchair user to their wheelchair alone. It is not a symbol of limitation, but part of everyday life. First and foremost, this is a person with their own character, tastes, dreams, and the right to feel natural in any space.",
